http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Water-for-every-house-by-April-end-says-KCR/article13987703.ece

Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao announced that water would be supplied to every household in Gajwel constituency by April 30.Addressing a gathering after laying the foundation stone for Konda Laxman Horticulture University at Mulugu mandal headquarters along with Union Agriculture Minister Radha Mohan Singh on Thursday, Mr. Rao said that very few forest colleges are there in the nation, with one in Tamil Naidu, and this will benefit the people surrounding other districts as well. The Chief Minister also announced that a cold storage unit at an estimated cost of Rs. 20 crore would come up at Ontimamidi Market so that the farmers can store their produce and sell the same when the market is ripe.Mr. Chandrasekhar Rao said that establishment of Forest College would increase the employment opportunities for the people of the State in the forest department across the nation.